quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  27,56,"But his people’s only response was to say, “Expel Lot’s followers from your land! They are a people who wish to remain chaste!”"
  27,57,"So We delivered him and his family, except his wife. We had destined her to be one of the doomed"
  27,58,And We poured upon them a rain ˹of brimstone˺. How evil was the rain of those who had been warned
  27,59,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Praise be to God, and peace be upon the servants He has chosen.” ˹Ask the disbelievers,˺ “Which is better: God or whatever ˹gods˺ they associate ˹with Him˺?”"
  27,60,"Or ˹ask them,˺ “Who created the heavens and the earth, and sends down rain for you from the sky, by which We cause delightful gardens to grow? You could never cause their trees to grow. Was it another god besides God?” Absolutely not! But they are a people who set up equals ˹to God˺"
  27,61,"Or ˹ask them,˺ “Who made the earth a place of settlement, caused rivers to flow through it, placed firm mountains upon it, and set a barrier between ˹fresh and salt˺ bodies of water? Was it another god besides God?” Absolutely not! But most of them do not know"
  27,62,"Or ˹ask them,˺ “Who responds to the distressed when they cry to Him, relieving ˹their˺ affliction, and ˹Who˺ makes you successors in the earth? Is it another god besides God? Yet you are hardly mindful!”"
  27,63,"Or ˹ask them,˺ “Who guides you in the darkness of the land and sea, and sends the winds ushering in His mercy? Is it another god besides God? Exalted is God above what they associate ˹with Him˺"
  27,64,"Or ˹ask them,˺ “Who originates the creation then resurrects it, and gives you provisions from the heavens and the earth? Is it another god besides God?” Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Show ˹me˺ your proof, if what you say is true.”"
  27,65,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “None in the heavens and the earth has knowledge of the unseen except God. Nor do they know when they will be resurrected"
  27,66,"No! Their knowledge of the Hereafter amounts to ignorance. In fact, they are in doubt about it. In truth, they are ˹totally˺ blind to it"
  27,67,"The disbelievers ask, “When we and our fathers are reduced to dust, will we really be brought forth ˹alive˺"
  27,68,"We have already been promised this, as well as our forefathers earlier. This is nothing but ancient fables!”"
  27,69,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Travel throughout the land and see the fate of the wicked.”"
  27,70,"Do not grieve for them, nor be distressed by their schemes"
  27,71,"They ask ˹the believers˺, “When will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?”"
  27,72,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Perhaps some of what you seek to hasten is close at hand.”"
  27,73,"Surely your Lord is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most of them are ungrateful"
  27,74,And surely your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they reveal
  27,75,For there is nothing hidden in the heavens or the earth without being ˹written˺ in a perfect Record
  27,76,"Indeed, this Quran clarifies for the Children of Israel most of what they differ over"
  27,77,And it is truly a guide and mercy for the believers
  27,78,"Your Lord will certainly judge between them by His justice, for He is the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  27,79,"So put your trust in God, for you are surely upon the ˹Path of˺ clear truth"
  27,80,You certainly cannot make the dead hear ˹the truth˺. Nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away
  27,81,"Nor can you lead the blind out of their misguidance. You can make none hear ˹the truth˺ except those who believe in Our revelations, ˹fully˺ submitting ˹to God˺"